      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Charging device structure description - Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "summary"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The A.C. generator has a multi-stage variable output voltage according to the power consumption to reduce fuel consumption by controlling the output appropriately. A battery sensor attached to the negative terminal of the battery measures current/voltage, battery temperature, and internal battery resistance and sends signals to the PGM-FI ECU. Based on the signals, the PGM-FI ECU sends appropriate power generation commands to the A.C. generator to generate the necessary power."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "*Variable control may not be possible depending on vehicle conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1909_3.0_jpn_11242749_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This A.C. generator records the following DTC at the time of failure, so please refer to the relevant DTC failure diagnosis."
